The paper discusses a novel learning structure for deep neural networks that addresses the limitations of backpropagation, which is a common technique used in machine learning and deep learning. The paper focuses on the efficiency and stability of the learning process, as well as the biological plausibility of the approach. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
